          "found : Kent, K.P. Introducing West African cloth, 1971: p. 3 (\"There is today a bewildering variety of textile styles, reflecting the differing cultural patterns of West Africa. Each major group (or \"tribe\") has its own distinctive type of weaving or design. The following text divides the cloth for descriptive purposes into four categories: 1. Men's narrow band cloth, woven on the horizontal treadle loom ...\") Also chapter one (\"Men's narrow band weaving.\")",
